    <item><title>Other</title>
      <author>Dahlia (Oopzs)</author>
      <description>&lt;article class=&#34;md-content__inner md-typeset&#34;&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New: Add autofocus for search input when modal opens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After clicking the &lt;code&gt;Search&lt;/code&gt; link, the search input in modal should be
autoselected for easier input.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to how HTML5 defines its semantics, the autofocus HTML attribute has no effect in Bootstrap modals. To achieve the same effect, use some custom JavaScript:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;pre class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;$(&#39;#myModal&#39;).on(&#39;shown.bs.modal&#39;, function () {
  $(&#39;#myInput&#39;).focus()
})&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ref:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://getbootstrap.com/javascript/#modals&#34;&gt;http://getbootstrap.com/javascript/#modals&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New: Add autofocus for search input in search.html.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr/&gt;

